# Smart Irrigation Monitoring System

## overview
The Smart Irrigation Monitoring System is an IoT-based project developed using ESP32 to monitor soil moisture levels and automate irrigation decisions. The system displays real-time soil moisture status on an OLED display and provides alerts through LEDs and a buzzer. The project is designed to improve water efficiency and support smart agriculture applications.

## Features
- Real-time soil moisture monitoring
- OLED display for live moisture readings
- Automatic irrigation status indication
- LED indicators for dry and wet soil conditions
- Buzzer alert for low moisture levels
- ESP32-based IoT prototype
- Wokwi simulation

## Components Used
- ESP32
- Soil Moisture Sensor
- OLED Display (SSD1306)
- Green LED
- Red LED
- Buzzer
- Jumper wires

## Software & Tools
- Arduino IDE
- Wokwi Simulator
- VS Code

## Project Structure
- ESP32 Arduino Code
- Wokwi Circuit Files
- Project Documentation (PDF)

## Working
1. The soil moisture sensor measures the moisture level.
2. ESP32 processes the sensor readings.
3. The OLED displays the moisture percentage and irrigation status.
4. LEDs indicate whether the soil is dry or sufficiently moist.
5. The buzzer alerts when irrigation is required.

## Applications
- Smart Agriculture
- Home Garden Automation
- Greenhouse Monitoring
- Water Conservation Systems

## Future Improvements
- Automatic water pump control using a relay
- Weather API integration for intelligent irrigation

